commitResults.messageTitle: Improve code quality by adding abstract classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Task class had redundant and confusing constructors and methods that are
no longer used, it acts solely as a parent class

Changing it into an abstract class prevents it from being accidentally
instantiated and makes the methods it holds look cleaner

additionally more magic numbers were found that were changed into
constants
renamed byeText Method to make it more descriptive

Previously without exception handling chatbot would crash when given
inputs that do not fit the right command structure

Added try ctach statements that will allow it to fail gracefully,
keeping the chatbot running for its next command. Giving instructions on
how to better give commands

Additionally, The exception handling for done and undone is required

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Exception handling for setDone and List methods
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously code's exception handling relied on multiple if/else blocks
this is extremely inefficient as one would have to account for all the
different ways the method can error. It also makes code hard to read
because of the if else logic

Exception handling is now  handled by try catch statements and custom
exceptions like ALreadyDoneExceptions.This makes code easier to read and
understand as well as easier to write

Previously methods in code have no exception handling or are handled by
multiple if else statements, resulting in code failing hard when
commands are not correct and code being messy and hard to read and inefficeint because of
the multple if else statements

adding of branch-Level-5 that adds exception handling of addtask, and
set as done methods using try catch statements and custom Exceptions.
Makes code more readable and efficient

previously all java codes situated in one java file which made structure
of code messy and hard to read

Now with packages code is easier to read and classes are easier to find
chatBot can be scaled up more easily

previously list was reliant on fixed array of 100 items

by implementing colelction Arraylist maintaining array is simpler and

Previously all data in the session are not saved. Hence, everytime the

Through the implementation of the saving method the user can now save
his data across multiple uses
